<br>
Hehe, well not really. Clerics only get PB AoEs, so they have to nuke from melee range, and their spells have a long casting time and refresh. It's really better to do as I described and drag your quad through their PB. They don't get hurt, and if you time it right, they get the kill, which makes them like the grouping arrangement. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=alphie>Alphie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/22/02 3:29:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm21.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> quading clerics</span><hr size=1> Well she actually aoe stuns...then walks in melee range and pbaoe nukes.  She has plenty of time to finish what shes doing before snare wears off.  She takes a few hits throughout the battle but nothing a cleric with 2500+hps can't deal with.  Having her doing it herself: <br>
1) Gives her much greater sense of pride rather than feeling like a flappy that nukes. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  (Guess she almost feels wizard-like /grin )<br>
2) Allows her to keep faction with otters while I'm hated like an ebayed monk.<br>
3) Less quad complications like mobs shifting targets and having to regather them and such.<br>
<br>
